metadata.title: Ryan Navion
aws::graph::propositions: # Ryan Navion Aircraft Variants
Navion G Rangemaster is a redesigned aircraft by Navion Aircraft Company.
Navion G Rangemaster has a 260hp Continental IO-470H engine.
Navion G Rangemaster has integral cabin tanks.
Navion G Rangemaster has integral tip tanks.
121 Navion G Rangemaster aircraft were built.
Some Navion G Rangemaster aircraft were built as the Rangemaster G-1.
Rangemaster G-1 has a modified fin.
Navion H Rangemaster is a variant of Navion G.
Navion H Rangemaster has a 285hp Continental IO-520B engine.
60 Navion H Rangemaster aircraft were built.
An additional Navion H Rangemaster aircraft was built by the Navion Rangemaster Aircraft Company in 1974.
Ryan Model 72 is a modified Navion B.
Ryan Model 72 was modified as a two-seat trainer.
Ryan Model 72 was created for a United States Navy competition.
Ryan Model 72 competed with the Temco Model 33 Plebe.
Camair Twin Navion is a twin engine conversion.
Camair 480 is a variant of Camair Twin Navion.
Camair 480 has 2 Continental O-470-B engines.
Each Continental O-470-B engine in Camair 480 produces 240 hp.
Camair 480C is a variant of Camair Twin Navion.
Camair 480C has 2 Continental IO-470 engines.
Each Continental IO-470 engine in Camair 480C produces 260 hp.
Approximately 25 Camair Twin Navion aircraft were built.

text:
Navion G Rangemaster
Redesigned aircraft by Navion Aircraft Company with 260hp Continental IO-470H engine, integral cabin and tip tanks, 121, some built as the Rangemaster G-1 with a modified fin.
Navion H Rangemaster
Navion G with a 285hp Continental IO-520B engine, 60 built, an additional aircraft was built by the Navion Rangemaster Aircraft Company in 1974.
Ryan Model 72
One Navion B was modified as two-seat trainer for a United States Navy competition with the Temco Model 33 Plebe.
Camair Twin Navion
twin engine conversion Camair 480, 2 Continental O-470-B, 240 hp each. Camair 480C, 2 Continental IO-470- 260 hp each. 25+- built.
